5. **Real-time Tracking**: Apps can use location data to provide users with real-time tracking information. For example, a ride-sharing app can use location data to provide users with real-time updates on the location of their driver.
6. **Location-based Social Sharing**: Apps can use location data to enable users to share their location with friends and family. For example, a social media app can allow users to share their location with friends and family, making it easier to meet up and connect.
7. **Personalized Navigation**: Apps can use location data to provide users with personalized navigation instructions. For example, a mapping app can use location data to provide users with the most efficient route to their destination.
